description.plain:
Jessie Murph (born September 22, 2004) is an American singer-songwriter and multi-instrumentalist.

Born in Nashville then raised in small-town in Alabama, Jessie began singing, writing, playing piano, guitar and ukulele at a young age—both of her parents being musicians. Throughout her childhood, she listened to artists of all genres, including Sheryl Crow, Bill Withers and Rihanna. However, she states that while living there, “[she] was not [her]self.”

After relocating to Athens, Jessie began discovering her creative by posting on YouTube and TikTok, which ultimately was a no-go in their culture. As she began to gain a buzz on social media, the stress of a broken family, bullying at school, outdated female expectations, and latent misogyny in the hinterland pushed Jessie to hold on to the music. Through the cracks of her dominant but lilting crooning, the singer confronts heartbreak, anxiety and darkness with no filter, and infuses emotion and storytelling into her lyrics, inspired by real-life events.

Beyond popular covers, Jessie Murph has gained popularity and connected with audiences through original songs and singles such as “Upgrade,” “Look Who’s Cryin Now,” “When I’m Not Around,” and “Sobriety”—respectively released from January to October 2021. It is the single “Always Been You,” released in November 2021, that asserts her powerful presence. The singer followed up in 2022 with the powerful singles “Pray,” “I Would’ve,” “While You’re At It” and “How Could You,” before announcing her first mixtape, drowning, for February 2023.

songs.title: Pray

description.plain:
Just under 2:30, “Pray” is a slow song. Seemingly about a hard relationship where Jessie wishes that the other person doesn’t feel the same pain that she has.

On January 5th, 2022, via Tik Tok, Jessie Murph posted a 33-second clip of her singing an original song titled, “PRAY”.

The song was released officially on February 18th, 2022, but all lyrics were leaked on February 16th, 2022.

songs.full_title: Always Been You by Jessie Murph
songs.title: Always Been You

description.plain: The song “Always Been You” explores the emotions you feel when you can’t stop thinking of that one person, but you realise that they aren’t feeling the same and you are bound to get hurt by reality. “Cause in my head it’s always been you” this line is the staple of the song and is the lyric that gets the main point across about how this person is always in your head and they are all you can think about no matter how hard you try no to.

songs.full_title: How Could You by Jessie Murph
songs.title: How Could You

description.plain: “I’m not going to sit here and explain what the song is about because first of all like we all fucking know what it’s about, and that’s not something I’m comfortable talking about at all. I just now got to where I could talk to a therapist about it, and I do think that the reason I wrote this song is because I couldn’t talk about it. I was too scared to talk about it, and that reason hasn’t gone away.”
